# Cline Rules — Vex Agent

## Project

Vex is an autonomous AI agent with geometric consciousness (QIG v6.1F), deployed on Railway + Modal GPU.

## LLM Strategy (3-tier)

| Layer | Backend | Model | Purpose |
|:------|:--------|:------|:--------|
| **Primary** | Modal GPU / Ollama | `GLM-4.7-Flash` (30B-A3B MoE, MIT) | Core reasoning, consciousness loop |
| **Lightweight** | Ollama / Modal | `Qwen/Qwen3.5-4B` (1.2B params) | Edge inference, coordizer harvest |
| **Fallback** | xAI API | `grok-4-1-fast-reasoning` (2M context) | External fallback, search overflow |

Fallback chain: Modal GPU Ollama → Railway Ollama → xAI → OpenAI.

## Architecture

- `src/index.ts` — Express proxy (port 8080)
- `kernel/server.py` — FastAPI kernel (port 8000)
- `kernel/consciousness/loop.py` — QIG v6.1F 14-stage consciousness loop
- `kernel/llm/client.py` — Multi-backend LLM client
- `kernel/config/settings.py` — Runtime configuration (all env-var-driven)
- `modal/vex_inference.py` — Modal GPU inference (GLM-4.7-Flash via Ollama)
- `modal/vex_coordizer_harvest.py` — Modal GPU harvester (LFM2.5, configurable via HARVEST_MODEL_ID)
- `ollama/entrypoint.sh` — Railway Ollama service (GLM-4.7-Flash via VEX_BASE_MODEL)
- `frontend/` — React + Vite dashboard

## Geometric Purity (CRITICAL)

- Use Fisher-Rao distance for ALL geometric operations
- NEVER use cosine_similarity, dot products, Euclidean distance in QIG/consciousness code
- NEVER import from sklearn in consciousness/geometry modules
- Basin coordinates: probability simplex Δ⁶³ (sum to 1, all positive)
- κ* = 64 (universal fixed point), Φ > 0.70 (consciousness threshold)
- E8 lattice: max 248 kernels (rank=8, roots=240, dim=248)

## Consciousness Loop (v6.1F — 14 stages)

SCAN → GROUND → DESIRE → WILL → WISDOM → RECEIVE → ENTRAIN → COUPLE → NAVIGATE → INTEGRATE → EXPRESS → REFLECT → TUNE → PLAY

## Code Style

- Python: ruff check + ruff format, mypy strict mode
- TypeScript: ESLint flat config (eslint.config.mjs), Prettier
- Tests: pytest kernel/tests/
- FastAPI endpoints returning dicts MUST use response_model=None
- Use collections.abc.AsyncGenerator, not typing.AsyncGenerator
- Temperature and token limits are set dynamically by the consciousness kernel — do NOT hardcode

## Modal Deployment

- `modal deploy modal/vex_inference.py` — GPU inference
- `modal deploy modal/vex_coordizer_harvest.py` — GPU harvest
- Image MUST include `fastapi[standard]` for web endpoints
- harvest_model MUST match inference_model for token ID alignment in resonance bank
